x4freetext: .The Reaction on
Nickel.
.`Overlaid Alice`.
Remarks of V. Mclane are Included
Last checking has been done.
. The Uncertainty of Target Thickness.
. The Uncertainty of Gamma-Rays Intensity.
. The Uncertainty of Current Beam.
. Total Uncertaities. The Information About
`Data-Err` was Extracted by Compiler from Brinkmann`S
Thesis.
Beam Energy Uncertainty As It has Been Shown
By the Authors.
The Excitation Functions were Measured Using the
Stacked-Foil Technique.
For Each Target Element 2 Types of Stacks were Used
In Order to Avoid Too Large Errors in the Particle
Energies Due to the Effect of Range Straggling. The
First One had to Degrade the Alpha-Energy from 172.5
MeV to About 80 MeV, the Second One from 90 to About
15 MeV. Each Stack Consisted of a Number of Target
Foils, Alternately Followed by a High Purity 25
Mumeters `Al` Catcher Foil and by Commercial Grade
`Al` Degrader Foils. For Manganese 25 Mumeters Foils
Of a `Mn-Ni` Alloy, Containing 88 Per Cent `Mn` and
12 Per Cent `Ni` were Used.
For the `Mn`-Iradiated the Contribution of `Ni` to
The Production of Radionuclides had to be Corrected
For Using the Earlier Determined Excitations For
Alpha-Induced Reactions on `Ni`.
Shielded
